        <body>
            <p rend="align(center)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>Sunday</date>, of Portion
                "Teruma", <date>1854</date></p>
            <p rend="align(center)">(about <date>February</date>)</p>
            <p>About a sermon of <persName>Kalischers</persName>, preached<lb/> in
                    <placeName>Phila.</placeName> &amp; published in Occident, on<lb/> subject of
                Talmudic study.</p>
            <p><persName><hi rend="underline">Rabbi Mewlel Goldschmit</hi></persName> writes in
                refutation<lb/> of <persName>Kalischer's</persName> "Reform" views
                <del>abo</del><lb/> regarding the authority of Oral Law.<lb/> Mentions fact that in Occident<lb/>
                <persName>Leeser</persName> had already refuted <persName>Kalischer</persName><lb/>
                calls Reform a threat to life<lb/> of Jewish People.</p>
            <div>
                <p>
                    <ref target="Occident_PDFs/Occ_11_10.pdf">The above text refers to Occident
                        Volume 11 No. 10 pages 552 through 566. Click here to view.</ref>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
